# Git Hygiene Rules

- Preserve unrelated user changes.
- Keep diffs focused.
- Keep the main thread focused on decisions, edits, validation, and final synthesis.
- Use subagents for bounded, read-only reconnaissance, test triage, docs review, or issue/PR summarization when that keeps bulky exploration out of the main thread.
- Give subagents explicit scope and verify their findings before editing.
- Before claiming done, state validation commands and results.
- When the user asks to commit, push, or publish, prefer `uv run scaffold-guard publish --message "<message>" --all` after reviewing the dirty scope, or use repeated `--file PATH` options for an exact scope. Use `--push-only` only when the working tree is clean.
